# Per-observable Functional Jacobian fixture (GH #76 task 2).
#
# Exercises the .net product rule rate = func(observables)·∏reactants together
# with the observable-group chain rule:
#   - rxn 1 (A+B -> C) has functional rate fr() = k1*Atot and a bimolecular
#     species factor A*B, so rate1 = k1*Atot*A*B.
#   - Atot = A + 3*C is an AGGREGATING observable, so ∂fr/∂C is non-zero even
#     though C is not a reactant of rxn 1 (pure term-A column).
#   - A is BOTH a reactant and in the observable group (term A + term B column).
#   - B is a reactant only (pure term-B column).
#   - rxn 2 (C -> A+B) is Elementary, mixing the closed-form and functional paths.
begin parameters
    1 k1 0.001
    2 k2 0.05
end parameters
begin species
    1 A() 50
    2 B() 30
    3 C() 10
end species
begin functions
    1 fr() k1*Atot
end functions
begin reactions
    1 1,2 3 fr   #A_plus_B_to_C
    2 3 1,2 k2   #C_to_A_plus_B
end reactions
begin groups
    1 Atot 1,3*3
end groups
